-- Janney Montgomery Scott Hires Former Cantor Fitzgerald Director Jay Meaney
-- B y   J o h n   D e t r i x h e
-- 2010-10-14T20:26:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/janney-montgomery-scott-hires-former-cantor-fitzgerald-director-jay-meaney.html
Janney Montgomery Scott LLC, the
178-year-old Philadelphia brokerage, has hired  Jay Meaney ,
formerly a director at Cantor Fitzgerald & Co., as managing
director of institutional agency trading.  Meaney, 57, will work in Philadelphia in the company’s
Janney Capital Markets unit and report to  Steve Genyk , head of
fixed-income capital markets, according to a statement to be
officially released tomorrow. The firm has more than 20
employees in institutional fixed-income sales and trading, the
statement said.  “Our institutional fixed income business has grown
tremendously over the past two years,” Genyk said in the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
